body: Seems a typo on the cpuinfo code, no real overread possible. Let me study how to get around this.

This warning does not affect the build, but the following errors occur when building armv6 wheels:
```shell
[ 98%] Building CXX object CMakeFiles/onnxruntime_pybind11_state.dir/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/python/onnxruntime_pybind_exceptions.cc.o
[100%] Building CXX object CMakeFiles/onnxruntime_pybind11_state.dir/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/python/onnxruntime_pybind_iobinding.cc.o

/usr/lib/gcc/armv6-alpine-linux-musleabihf/11.2.1/../../../../armv6-alpine-linux-musleabihf/bin/ld: external/pytorch_cpuinfo/libcpuinfo.a(init.c.o): in function `cpuinfo_initialize':
init.c:(.text.cpuinfo_initialize+0x28): undefined reference to `cpuinfo_arm_linux_init'
/usr/lib/gcc/armv6-alpine-linux-musleabihf/11.2.1/../../../../armv6-alpine-linux-musleabihf/bin/ld: onnxruntime_pybind11_state.so: hidden symbol `cpuinfo_arm_linux_init' isn't defined
/usr/lib/gcc/armv6-alpine-linux-musleabihf/11.2.1/../../../../armv6-alpine-linux-musleabihf/bin/ld: final link failed: bad value
collect2: error: ld returned 1 exit status
make[2]: *** [CMakeFiles/onnxruntime_pybind11_state.dir/build.make:265: onnxruntime_pybind11_state.so] Error 1
make[1]: *** [CMakeFiles/Makefile2:1866: CMakeFiles/onnxruntime_pybind11_state.dir/all] Error 2
make: *** [Makefile:166: all] Error 2
```

DockerFile:
```shell
FROM alpine:edge

# Envirenment 
ENV ONNXRUNTIME_TAG=master

# 换源 & Install packages
RUN sed -i 's/dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org/mirrors.ustc.edu.cn/g' /etc/apk/repositories && \
    apk update && \
    apk add --update --no-cache openrc redis bash git tzdata nano openssh-client ca-certificates\
    file libidn2-dev libgsasl-dev krb5-dev zstd-dev nghttp2-dev zlib-dev brotli-dev \
    python3 py3-numpy-dev py3-pip py3-setuptools py3-wheel py3-opencv py3-pillow && \
    ln -s /usr/bin/python3 /usr/bin/python

# git clone onnxruntime & Pip install onnxruntime
RUN apk add --update --no-cache --virtual .build_deps cmake make perl autoconf g++ automake \
    linux-headers libtool util-linux libexecinfo-dev openblas-dev python3-dev \
    protobuf-dev date-dev gtest-dev eigen-dev && \
    git clone --depth 1 --branch $ONNXRUNTIME_TAG https://github.com./Microsoft/onnxruntime && \
    cd /onnxruntime && \
    git submodule update --init --recursive && \
    cd .. && \
    rm /onnxruntime/onnxruntime/test/providers/cpu/nn/string_normalizer_test.cc && \
    sed "s/    return filters/    filters += \[\'^test_strnorm.*\'\]\n    return filters/" \
    -i /onnxruntime/onnxruntime/test/python/onnx_backend_test_series.py && \
    echo 'add_subdirectory(${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}/external/nsync EXCLUDE_FROM_ALL)' >> /onnxruntime/cmake/CMakeLists.txt && \
    cmaketmp="-DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=MinSizeRel -Dprotobuf_WITH_ZLIB=OFF -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=/onnxruntime/build/tool.cmake \
    -Donnxruntime_ENABLE_PYTHON=ON -DPYTHON_EXECUTABLE=/usr/bin/python3 -Donnxruntime_BUILD_SHARED_LIB=OFF \
    -Donnxruntime_DEV_MODE=OFF -DONNX_CUSTOM_PROTOC_EXECUTABLE=/usr/bin/protoc -Donnxruntime_BUILD_UNIT_TESTS=OFF \
    -Donnxruntime_USE_PREINSTALLED_EIGEN=ON -Donnxruntime_PREFER_SYSTEM_LIB=ON -Deigen_SOURCE_PATH=/usr/include/eigen3" && \
    mkdir -p /onnxruntime/build && \
    echo "SET(CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME Linux)" > /onnxruntime/build/tool.cmake && \
    echo "SET(CMAKE_SYSTEM_VERSION 1)" >> /onnxruntime/build/tool.cmake && \
    echo "SET(CMAKE_C_COMPILER gcc)" >> /onnxruntime/build/tool.cmake && \
    echo "SET(CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER g++)" >> /onnxruntime/build/tool.cmake && \
    echo "SET(CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH_MODE_PROGRAM NEVER)" >> /onnxruntime/build/tool.cmake && \
    echo "SET(CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH_MODE_LIBRARY ONLY)" >> /onnxruntime/build/tool.cmake && \
    echo "SET(CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH_MODE_INCLUDE ONLY)" >> /onnxruntime/build/tool.cmake && \
    echo "SET(CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH_MODE_PACKAGE ONLY)" >> /onnxruntime/build/tool.cmake && \
    echo "SET(CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH /)" >> /onnxruntime/build/tool.cmake && \
    echo 'STRING(APPEND CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS " -Wno-deprecated-copy -Wno-unused-variable -Wno-psabi")' >> /onnxruntime/build/tool.cmake && \
    cd /onnxruntime/build && cmake ../cmake $cmaketmp && \
    make -j$(($(grep -c ^processor /proc/cpuinfo) - 0)) && python3 setup.py bdist_wheel && cd /; } && \
    apk del .build_deps && \
    apk add libprotobuf-lite && \
    pip install --no-cache-dir /onnxruntime/build/Linux/MinSizeRel/dist/onnxruntime*.whl && \
    ln -s $(python -c 'import warnings;warnings.filterwarnings("ignore");\
    from distutils.sysconfig import get_python_lib;print(get_python_lib())')/onnxruntime/capi/libonnxruntime_providers_shared.so /usr/lib && \
    cd / && rm -rf /onnxruntime

```
I can build libonnxruntime.so without problem on Linux ARM64. I am not familiar with python part of the build. We need to investigate more where the problem lies.
armv6 is not ARM64. We don't have an Linux ARMv6 pipeline, so I don't know if it could work.

> I can build libonnxruntime.so without problem on Linux ARM64. I am not familiar with python part of the build. We need to investigate more where the problem lies.

This warning does not affect the build on the ARM64, but I think it is a noticeable problem

> armv6 is not ARM64. We don't have an Linux ARMv6 pipeline, so I don't know if it could work.

When i build the arm wheel (either v6 or v7), the first 99% of the progress is smooth, only in the last 1% is the error that prompts the following `cpuinfo` initialization failure.

**Maybe I should open another issue? **
